## Glass in Dumplings, Metal in Cottage Cheese
The latest recalls expose a consistent failure in quality control, with the most egregious being products containing foreign objects. Ajinomoto Foods North America Inc. recalled multiple products, including vegetable fried rice and gyoza dumplings, due to glass fragments. Similarly, Albertsons Companies LLC issued a recall for cottage cheese due to metal pieces (a stainless steel spring, to be exact).

## Mustard Oil Misstep
Mangalm LLC has a recurring issue with its Tops GOLD pickles, consistently flagged for adulteration concerns related to erucic acid from mustard oil. This issue signals a systemic problem with ingredient sourcing.

## Chocolate Ladybugs and Allergen Troubles
Lidl US Trading struggled with its Favorina Chocolate Ladybugs, which failed proper allergen labeling by not disclosing the specific type of tree nut present. This oversight could have dire consequences for those with allergies.

## A Grim Report Card
Among the usual culprits, Ajinomoto Foods and Albertsons lead the recall leaderboard for Class I incidents this year. Moonlight Packing Corporation and Diva Fam Inc have also earned low scores, indicating significant quality control failures.
